    "value": "OpenClaw integrates with GitHub Copilot to leverage its AI coding assistant features for a wide range of agent-automation and coding scenarios. Here’s a summary of common use cases and scenarios for using the GitHub Copilot CLI in OpenClaw, according to official documentation and real-world implementations:\n\n### 1. Connecting GitHub Copilot to OpenClaw\nOpenClaw can use GitHub Copilot as the AI model provider through two main methods:\n- **Built-in provider (`github-copilot`)**: Uses a device-login flow (no VS Code required), ideal for simple setups.\n- **Copilot Proxy plugin**: Leverages the VS Code Copilot Proxy extension for organizations already using VS Code heavily and needing custom routing or proxying.\n\nSetup involves running commands like:\n```sh\nopenclaw models auth login-github-copilot\nopenclaw models set github-copilot/gpt-4o\n```\nYou can select models based on your subscription, such as `gpt-4o`, or others like `gpt-4.1` if you encounter model-specific restrictions【3:0†GitHub Copilot - OpenClaw】【3:3†Setting Up GitHub Copilot in OpenClaw | OpenClaw】【3:4†Github Copilot - OpenClaw Docs | Learn OpenClaw】.\n\n### 2. Common Use Cases and Scenarios\n\n#### a. **AI Coding Assistant for Developers**\nOpenClaw agents can utilize Copilot to:\n- Auto-generate, review, or refactor code as part of pull request workflows.\n- Draft, summarize, and auto-document codebases or inline documentation.\n- Suggest fixes or improvements interactively via chat or terminal CLI.\n\n#### b. **Software Development Workflow Automation**\n- **Issue management:** Automatically triage, tag, and close stale issues in GitHub repositories.\n- **Automated PR review:** Generate review comments or checklists for pull requests using Copilot’s summarization.\n- **CI/CD Integration:** Use agents to monitor build statuses or trigger deployments based on analysis or Copilot directives【3:6†34 OpenClaw Use Cases: What People Actually Do With Their AI Agent】.\n\n#### c. **Productivity and “Chief of Staff” Agents**\nOpenClaw X Copilot agents can automate:\n- Personal task lists: Integrate with Todoist, Notion, or similar tools to auto-create and update tasks based on Slack/Telegram/Email conversations.\n- Meeting notes: Summarize transcripts and extract action items using Copilot’s LLM.\n- Daily briefings: Aggregate data from calendars, emails, and project management tools, delivering actionable summaries in chat.\n\n#### d. **Research and Data Analysis**\n- **Semantic memory search:** Use Copilot to find, summarize, or explain documentation, code, or knowledge base articles.\n- **Automated data analytics:** Agents can provide code scripts or analysis for requested datasets via CLI prompts.\n\n#### e. **Automation for Social Media and Content**\n- Auto-draft and schedule posts for platforms like Twitter/X, Xiaohongshu, and others using pipeline agents.\n- Summarize or draft content based on trending topics or raw source material.\n- Automated market research: Copilot-driven analysis and comparison of products, prices, or customer feedback【3:1†avenstack/awesome-openclaw-cases】【3:6†34 OpenClaw Use Cases: What People Actually Do With Their AI Agent】.\n\n### 3. Typical Command Line Patterns\n- Login: `openclaw models auth login-github-copilot`\n- Set default model: `openclaw models set github-copilot/gpt-4o`\n- Use specific profiles: `openclaw models auth login-github-copilot --profile-id github-copilot:work --yes`\n- Troubleshoot or switch models as needed if rate limits or model errors occur【3:3†Setting Up GitHub Copilot in OpenClaw | OpenClaw】【3:0†GitHub Copilot - OpenClaw】.\n\n### 4. Things to Consider\n- Model access is tied to your Copilot subscription plan—some advanced models may require a higher tier.\n- Device login requires interactive TTY (can't be headless, which can affect CI/CD automation).\n- Some guides note a free/unlimited usage for certain Copilot models (`gpt-4o`, `gpt-5-mini`), though this depends on your plan and how OpenClaw handles requests【3:5†Setting up OpenClaw and Integrating GitHub Copilot for Unlimited Free ...】.\n\n### 5. Real-World Implementations and Exploration\n- The OpenClaw community maintains a [curated use case repository](https://github.com/avenstack/awesome-openclaw-cases), documenting patterns like automation pipelines, observability, smart home integration, and productization research flows. Use cases include family digital scrapbooks, AI social posting, multi-agent orchestration, and predictive market trading【3:1†avenstack/awesome-openclaw-cases】.\n\n---\n\n#### For more in-depth scenarios and real use case walkthroughs, see:\n- [OpenClaw’s official Copilot documentation](https://docs.openclaw.ai/providers/github-copilot)\n- [Awesome OpenClaw Use Cases on GitHub](https://github.com/avenstack/awesome-openclaw-cases)\n- Community posts summarizing [34 practical use cases](https://openclaw.rocks/blog/openclaw-use-cases) in actual environments\n\nIf you’d like usage scripts or tailored setup guidance for a specific workflow, let me know!",
